ENTRY       EC 3.1.16.1                 Enzyme
NAME        spleen exonuclease;
            3'-exonuclease;
            spleen phosphodiesterase;
            3'-nucleotide phosphodiesterase;
            phosphodiesterase II
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on ester bonds;
            Exonucleases that are active with either ribo- or deoxyribonucleic acids and produce 3'-phosphomonoesters
REACTION    Exonucleolytic cleavage in the 5'- to 3'-direction to yield nucleoside 3'-phosphates
COMMENT     Preference for single-stranded substrate.
HISTORY     EC 3.1.16.1 created 1972 as EC 3.1.4.18, transferred 1978 to EC 3.1.16.1
REFERENCE   1
  AUTHORS   Bernardi, A. and Bernardi, G.
  TITLE     Spleen acid nuclease.
  JOURNAL   In: Boyer, P.D. (Ed.), The Enzymes, 3rd ed., vol. 4, Academic Press, New York, 1971, p. 329-336.
